      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@TomerCagan You may either: map the indices to the preferred order, if said order can be expressed as a function (to iterate the params in reverse, use IntStream.range(0, params.size()).map(i -&gt; params.size() - 1 - i)), or just provide your own range if the specific order is not something that can be mathematically derived from the result of IntStream.range(0, params.size()), like Stream.iterate(new int[] {0, 1}, ia -&gt; new int[] {ia[1], ia[0] + ia[1]}).mapToInt(ia -&gt; ia[0]).filter(i -&gt; i &lt; params.size()).limit(params.size()) if you want to iterate a subset of the params in Fibonacci order."
