  "title" : "Java 8 forEach with index",
  "body" : "<p>Is there a way to build a <code>forEach</code> method in Java 8 that iterates with an index? Ideally I'd like something like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>params.forEach((idx, e) -&gt; query.bind(idx, e));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The best I could do right now is:</p>\n\n<pre><code>int idx = 0;\nparams.forEach(e -&gt; {\n  query.bind(idx, e);\n  idx++;\n});\n</code></pre>\n"
